Job Posting Title:   SE_Simulation & Analysis Engineer_Experienced
Description: Deliver quality assured calculation models and results and propose where/when to perform specific simulation and analysis . Draw conclusions and make recommendations using control systems and function simulation and analyses. Perform analyses and deliver validated results with respect to design targets. Support continuous improvement of methods and tools. Act as technical expert for his/her discipline. Plan, lead and perform high complex simulations/analyses. Take responsibility for the fidelity of the simulations/analyses. Support project and design engineers in all stages of projects for technical solutions on varied complex level. Initiate and lead worldwide network. Drive innovation through collaboration with universities and external institutes or in-house developed tools. Make others engaged in innovation. Drive method and tool development globally. Train and mentor less experienced Simulation & Analysis Engineers globally. Provide input to Product and System Roadmaps. Perform project content evaluation and estimation in order to meet timeline and delivery. Perform method and tool development. On Experienced level applies practical knowledge typically obtained through education and work experience (position typically requires 2 to 5 years relevant experience). - Self-sufficient, takes lead on own tasks and able to work/plan independently.- Self-driven proactive engagement with learning opportunities and ongoing Experienced development. -
Honing skills in home discipline whilst growing a more general, broader view of wider TD/BA system.- Shows potential for longer-term development.

Take the opportunity to join the exciting change journey Powertrain Engineering (PE) is embarking on when creating the future powertrains for our customers as well as the future working place.

This is us at PE
We are proud product owners for components, systems as well as complete powertrains. We are accountable for the lifecycle management of our products, from advanced engineering, through product development into the maintenance phase.

We stand in front of significant challenges – where reducing transport emitted CO2 emissions is one of the biggest – and are now adapting to take this on by simplifying and empowering our organization and way of working.
In this position you will be part of an organization dedicated to technology as well as empowering and developing our employees. We always use customer satisfaction as the ultimate performance measurement. Complete Powertrain is a vital part of Powertrain Engineering and the section has the overall responsibility for the system integration of all components and systems which together build a Complete Powertrain delivery.  This includes the responsibility for features- and quality-fulfillment of the complete powertrain.

Responsibilities / Main tasks
We are looking for a simulation engineer to join our team Application Engineering & Simulation. Our team is the competence center when it comes to data analytics and complete vehicle simulation in powertrain engineering Sweden. In this position you will carry out complete powertrain simulations and support method development within this field.

Who are you?
We expect you to be a person with strong analytical skills and a will to deliver. We see that you as the candidate have domain knowledge about powertrains and preferably a good understanding for powertrain control systems besides this you like coding and scripting. A positive mindset “can do attitude” and team work characterizes your personal profile.
•    You are holding a MSc. in Mathematics, Physics, Computer Science, Mechanical or applicable engineering field together with at least 2-5 years of Professional experience.
•    Preferably you have worked with embedded vehicle SW in some context.
•    You have good skills in Control theory and Vehicle dynamics.
•    You like to collaborate with other teams in a large global organization and to expand your personal network.
•    If you have experience from truck driving this is considered meritorious.
•    You have good knowledge about or are very motivated to learn Matlab Simulink
•    You have good skills in Python.




Experienced: position typically requires 2 to 5 years relevant experience

Volvo Group is an equal opportunity employer that values diversity in our workplace and we welcome all applicants regardless of age, ethnicity, gender or cultural background.

